local BlockPlayer = require "actions/BlockPlayer" local NumScreen = require "actions/NumScreen" local Serial = require "actions/Serial" local Ease = require "actions/Ease" local Wait = require "actions/Wait" local Do = require "actions/Do"
return function(self) local wallLayer for _,layer in pairs(self.scene.map.layers) do if layer.name == "RightWall" then wallLayer = layer break end end
local onSuccess = Serial { Ease(self.scene.camPos, "x", -200, 1), Ease(wallLayer, "offsety", -32*3, 1), Ease(self.scene.camPos, "x", 0, 1), Do(function() self.scene.objectLookup.RightEntrance.y = self.scene.objectLookup.RightEntranceBlock.y self.scene.objectLookup.RightEntrance.object.y = self.scene.objectLookup.RightEntranceBlock.y self.scene.objectLookup.RightEntrance:updateCollision() self.scene.objectLookup.RightEntranceBlock:remove() end) } return BlockPlayer { Wait(0.8), NumScreen {prompt="Enter access code", expected="1683", success=onSuccess} } end
